--------------------------------------------------------------------
Simple three-state ion channel model using Sundials ODE Solver, 
Boost:Python and PyUblas

Gareth Ferneyhough, University of Nevada, Reno. 
gareth.ferneyhough@gmail.com
-------------------------------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
This requires Boost, Sundials ODE Solver, and PyUblas. They are 
available here:

	https://computation.llnl.gov/casc/sundials/download/download.html
	http://www.boost.org/
	git clone http://git.tiker.net/trees/pyublas.git
	
	
	
To build, either use CMake manually to generate a makefile
to build libModFossa.so, or use the included Eclipse project's 
Make Target, 'Run CMake'. Note that you must manually create a 
directory named 'build' in the project's root directory.
Then build the Make Target 'install', which will build libModFossa.so
and copy it into the 'Python' directory.

Running:
Run 'run.py' in the 'Python' directory. Make sure libModFossa.so is in 
the same directory. 
